** Dinobot growled and swung his tail in agitation as he heard both Iron 
Raptor's and Angel Primes transmission. Sever second later hearing another 
communication from their commander.
He was approaching her position, noticing faintly that Tavatron had beaten 
him to it.
Angel Prime's transmission had seemed like a challenge towards the commander 
and her abilities, and even though he didn't agree with the Maximals actions 
so far, he had to admit that in a sense their commander was weak. But only 
as far as compassion was concerned.
So what if they lost one? The remainder would go on to engage the enemy!
However...the battle was already lost. It had been ever since Oblitertron 
had formed and demolished a fair number of the Maximals.
The Cybertronian Fire was already in a wreck. There was a 90% chance of no 
victory at this time.
Dinobot growled as he walked up to the crowd which had gathered around the 
commander, glaring towards FZ and charging up his optic laser just in case.
There was an uneasy feeling in the air and it was either a sense of the 
people around him or a feeling of his own. There was no telling with so many 
bots about him, even though they equaled less then 15.
Dinobot stopped and looked back across the field, already in the position in 
which he had been ordered to be in. By the commander's side. He glanced 
towards Tavatron and saw her stance, ready for battle. He was also ready, 
but was not so obvious.**
